 966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.9961342472055902, \"rank\": 0.002943219956303289, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both de Celis Montalban and Frankel also missed out on semifinal spots, as they finished 19th and 21st overall respectively.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Frankel\", \"score\": 0.7484402616640518, \"rank\": 0.33550512946118477, \"text\": \"Frankel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Frankel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Frankel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finishing with the fastest overall time in the heats was American Jack Alexy.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999346860461741, \"rank\": 5.028265647673727e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9945043278307946, \"rank\": 0.003818380641819599, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alexy won heat eight in 47.57 to book his place in the semifinals.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The other swimmers among the top five overall were Maxime Grousset of France (47.70, heat eight), David Popovici of Romania (47.92, heat nine), Nander Nemeth of Hungary (47.93, heat nine) and Jordan Crooks of the Cayman 