gled to find his top gear and finished behind the pack in the eight-man field.\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3205, \"end\": 3211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\", \"score\": 0.9994633244775133, \"rank\": 0.0005106879885172033, \"text\": \"Carter\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Carter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spain's Sergio de Celis Montalban won the heat in 48.49 seconds, with Israel's Tomer Frankel second in 48.66 seconds.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3330, \"end\": 3335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.985593111392341, \"rank\": 0.014599047588132453, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3354, \"end\": 3363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodriguez,_Rizal\", \"score\": 0.9954622884567246, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Montalban\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodriguez,_Rizal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodriguez,_Rizal\"}, {\"begin\": 3400, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999114154959957, \"rank\": 8.859233073231498e-05, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carter was the first Trinidad and Tobago athlete to qualify for the Paris games, and came into the meet with the third-best entry time among the eight swimmers - a 48.16-seconds clocking.\", \"from\": 344